</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- mm. 1–4: Light I-V-IV-ii-V texture, RH 2-note open 5ths, LH root+5th+oct
- mm. 5–8: Introduce vi substitutions for F#°; m8 sus4→resolved cadence
- mm. 9–16: Sequence repeat; m12 IΔ arpeggio for color; m13 IV+iii parallel 3rds; m16 vi7 sustained for E-maj sub
- mm. 17–24: Build to climax; m18 ii7 rich 3-note RH; m19 V→V7; m21 full IV+ii with LH 4 notes; m24 pedal G1 entry for final cadence

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m5→m6: common tone B4 held RH through I to I
- m13→m14: IV→iii inner voice C5 steps to B4 (smooth)
- m22→m23: V F#4 held across bar (common tone)
- m24: pedal G1 added only at final cadence (lever harp omits; pedal harp reinforces)

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1–8: sparse (2-note RH, 3-note LH), introduce the theme
- mm. 9–16: moderate (2-3 note RH, 3-4 note LH), richer at m12 (IΔ)
- mm. 17–24: full (3-note RH, 4-note LH), climax at m18 ii7; final cadence with pedal
-->
